README.md
     1→# Versioning Library for Go
     2→
     3→![Build Status](https://github.com/hashicorp/go-version/actions/workflows/go-tests.yml/badge.svg)
     4→[![Go Reference](https://pkg.go.dev/badge/github.com/hashicorp/go-version.svg)](https://pkg.go.dev/github.com/hashicorp/go-version)
     5→
     6→go-version is a library for parsing versions and version constraints,
     7→and verifying versions against a set of constraints. go-version
     8→can sort a collection of versions properly, handles prerelease/beta
     9→versions, can increment versions, etc.
    10→
    11→Versions used with go-version must follow [SemVer](http://semver.org/).
    12→
    13→## Installation and Usage
    14→
    15→Package documentation can be found on
    16→[Go Reference](https://pkg.go.dev/github.com/hashicorp/go-version).
    17→
    18→Installation can be done with a normal `go get`:
    19→
    20→```
    21→$ go get github.com/hashicorp/go-version
    22→```
    23→
    24→#### Version Parsing and Comparison
    25→
    26→```go
    27→v1, err := version.NewVersion("1.2")
    28→v2, err := version.NewVersion("1.5+metadata")
    29→
    30→// Comparison example. There is also GreaterThan, Equal, and just
    31→// a simple Compare that returns an int allowing easy >=, <=, etc.
    32→if v1.LessThan(v2) {
    33→    fmt.Printf("%s is less than %s", v1, v2)
    34→}
    35→```
    36→
    37→#### Version Constraints
    38→
    39→```go
    40→v1, err := version.NewVersion("1.2")
    41→
    42→// Constraints example.
    43→constraints, err := version.NewConstraint(">= 1.0, < 1.4")
    44→if constraints.Check(v1) {
    45→	fmt.Printf("%s satisfies constraints %s", v1, constraints)
    46→}
    47→```
    48→
    49→#### Version Sorting
    50→
    51→```go
    52→versionsRaw := []string{"1.1", "0.7.1", "1.4-beta", "1.4", "2"}
    53→versions := make([]*version.Version, len(versionsRaw))
    54→for i, raw := range versionsRaw {
    55→    v, _ := version.NewVersion(raw)
    56→    versions[i] = v
    57→}
    58→
    59→// After this, the versions are properly sorted
    60→sort.Sort(version.Collection(versions))
    61→```
    62→
    63→## Issues and Contributing
    64→
    65→If you find an issue with this library, please report an issue. If you'd
    66→like, we welcome any contributions. Fork this library and submit a pull
    67→request.
